  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Benin Floods</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Benin Floods program focuses on food distribution* and cash distribution in some 928 households in 7 villages in Aguegues commune. Following the recommendations of the post cash distribution study, the second round took place from 8 to10 March for a total number of 1127 households, including the co-spouses. Cash amounts distributed per household total the estimated cost to feed a family of five for 1 month based on market prices. CARE also trained its staff in malnutrition detection and continues a malnutrition detection operation (MUAC) for children between 6 and 59 months old. Detected cases are referred to the health centers supported by UNICEF for treatment of malnutrition in the Oueme department. Meanwhile, in the Zou department, where the system is not yet in place, contacts have been taken with local private/faith based institutions where the CARE team temporarily refers the severe malnutrition cases.</narrative>
  </description>
